{
  "A linear-quadratic system can have how many solutions?": "",
  "0, 1, or 2 solutions": "",
  "How do you solve a linear-quadratic system?": "",
  "Substitution: set the linear equation equal to the quadratic and solve": "",
  "What are solutions graphically?": "",
  "The intersection points of the line and parabola": "",
  "If a line is tangent to a parabola:": "",
  "The system has exactly 1 solution": "",
  "If a line doesn't intersect a parabola:": "",
  "The system has no solution": "",
  "Solve: y = x², y = x + 2": "",
  "x² = x + 2 → x² − x − 2 = 0 → (x−2)(x+1) = 0 → x = 2 or x = −1": "",
  "Solve: y = x² − 1, y = 3": "",
  "x² − 1 = 3 → x² = 4 → x = ±2": "",
  "A system of two quadratics can have:": "",
  "Can a quadratic-quadratic system have more than 2 solutions?": "",
  "No — two parabolas can intersect at most twice": "",
  "Solve: y = x² + 1, y = 2x + 1": "",
  "x² + 1 = 2x + 1 → x² − 2x = 0 → x(x − 2) = 0 → x = 0 or x = 2": ""
